mpire in western Europe, from which the country of France takes its name.","English (of Norman origin), Dutch, and German: from the personal name <i>Frank</i> (Norman French <i>Franco</i>, ancient Germanic <i>Franko</i>), in origin an ethnic name for a Frank, or from German <i>Franke</i> ‘Frank(ish), Franconian’ (compare 1 above). This also came to be used as an adjective meaning ‘free, open-hearted, generous’ (Middle English and Old French <i>franc</i> ‘free’, i.e. not a serf or slave), deriving from the fact that in Frankish Gaul only people of Frankish race enjoyed the status of fully free men. As a surname of German origin it is also found (in both possible meanings; see 1 above) in France (Alsace and Lorraine). Compare   Franc   and   Franck  ."]}]},{"name":"Frances","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Feminine form of   Francis .  In the 16th century the two spellings were used indiscriminately for both sexes, the distinction in spelling not being established until the 17th century."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705195,"age":31,"year":"1382","julianDay":2225826,"title":"Wycliffe's Bible","description":"John Wycliffe, English theologian and professor at the University of Oxford, completed a translation of the Bible from the Latin Vulgate into Middle English. This translation is known as Wycliffe's Bible and was completed around 1382.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wycliffe%27s_Bible","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Wycliffe's Bible","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705197,"age":104,"year":"1455","julianDay":2252488,"title":"Wars of the Roses","description":"Wars of the Roses was a series of English civil wars for control of the throne of England between the royal families House of Lancaster and the House of York. The name of the war was derived as the red rose was the symbol of the Lancastrians and the white rose was the symbol of the Yorks.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/british-history/wars-of-the-roses","urlTitle":"History - Wars of the Roses","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Frances Franke was born about 1351, in Grimsby, Lincolnshire, England as the daughter of Sir William Franke and -. She married Sir Edmund Pierrepont about 1370. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 1 daughter."},"et":{"about 1351–":"umbes 1351–Surnud","1351–Female":"1351–Surnud","1350–1422":"1350–1422","1374–Female":"1374–Surnud","1390–1452":"1390–1452","1330–Male":"1330–Surnud","–Female":"Surnud","about 1370":"umbes 1370","about 1390":"umbes 1390","1330":"1330","1374":"1374","1351":"1351","1350":"1350","1382":"1382","1390":"1390","1455":"1455","1422":"1422","1452":"1452","about 1374":"umbes 1374","about 1351":"umbes 1351","Grimsby, Lincolnshire, England":"Grimsby, Lincolnshire, England","Holme Pierrepont, Nottinghamshire, England":"Holme Pierrepont, Nottinghamshire, England"},"fi":{"about 1351–":"noin 1351–Kuollut","1351–Female":"1351–Kuollut","1350–1422":"1350–1422","1374–Female":"1374–Kuollut","1390–1452":"1390–1452","1330–Male":"1330–Kuollut","–Female":"Kuollut","about 1370":"noin 1370","about 1390":"noin 1390","1330":"1330","1374":"1374","1351":"1351","1350":"1350","1382":"1382","1390":"1390","1455":"1455","1422":"1422","1452":"1452","about 1374":"noin 1374","about 1351":"noin 1351","Grimsby, Lincolnshire, England":"Grimsby, Lincolnshire, England","Holme Pierrepont, Nottinghamshire, England":"Holme Pierrepont, Nottinghamshire, England"},"fr":{"about 1351–":"environ 1351–Décédée","1351–Female":"1351–Décédée","1350–1422":"1350–1422","1374–Female":"1374–Décédée","1390–1452":"1390–1452","1330–Male":"1330–Décédé","–Female":"Décédée","about 1370":"environ 1370","about 1390":"environ 1390","1330":"1330","1374":"1374","1351":"1351","1350":"1350","1382":"1382","1390":"1390","1455":"1455","1422":"1422","1452":"1452","about 1374":"environ 1374","about 1351":"environ 1351","Grimsby, Lincolnshire, England":"Grimsby, Lincolnshire, Angleterre"